From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 21:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] rockchip: match the SARADC by driver, not by node name

setup_boot_mode()'s weak rockchip_dnl_key_pressed() locates the SARADC by
walking UCLASS_ADC and comparing dev->name against "saradc". dev->name is the
device-tree *node* name -- lists_bind_fdt() takes it from ofnode_get_name() --
so the comparison only succeeds on SoCs whose node is spelled saradc@...,
which today means rk3288 and rk3399.

Every SoC from rk3568 onward follows the generic-node-name convention and
declares the block as

	saradc: adc@2ae00000 { ... };

where "saradc" is a *label*: it exists only in __symbols__ and never reaches
dev->name. The match can therefore never succeed on rk3568, rk3588 or rk3576.
The function falls through to -ENODEV, warns "no saradc device found", and
reports the download key as unpressed -- so the BootROM-download key is
silently dead on those SoCs whether or not the board wires one up, and no
amount of enabling CONFIG_SARADC_ROCKCHIP or setting the node status to okay
brings it back.

Match on the driver instead. Every Rockchip SARADC binds
U_BOOT_DRIVER(rockchip_saradc) whatever its node is called, so this finds the
device under both the old and the new spelling and drops the dependency on
device-tree cosmetics.
---
 arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
index 1563b1bd..be131b80 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
@@ -51,7 +51,7 @@ __weak int rockchip_dnl_key_pressed(void)
 
 	ret = -ENODEV;
 	uclass_foreach_dev(dev, uc) {
-		if (!strncmp(dev->name, "saradc", 6)) {
+		if (!strcmp(dev->driver->name, "rockchip_saradc")) {
 			ret = adc_channel_single_shot(dev->name, 1, &val);
 			break;
 		}
